>Thermostats almost always fail in the open (hot) position.  So if you adjust
>your thermostat on a cold engine (ie. with the flaps closed) then they'll
>never open!

Yeah there is a measurement for the thermostat when it is cold. Measure 
with caliper, tape measure, or ruler. It's in the Bentley and possibly 
mentioned in layman's terms in Muir's book among others.




